FT  02 MAY 91 / International Company News: New head at Paramount unit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PARAMOUNT Commun-ications, the US publishing and entertainment company, has
appointed Mr Brandon Tartikoff to head its Paramount Pictures unit, writes
Karen Zagor.
The move ends a month of speculation about who would succeed Mr Frank
Mancuso as head of the studio. In a surprise move, Mr Mancuso was eased out
as Paramount Pictures chairman in March when Mr Stanley Jaffe was appointed
above him as president and chief operating officer of the parent company. Mr
Mancuso resigned shortly after the appointment and has filed a Dollars 45m
lawsuit against Paramount.
Mr Tartikoff, 42, has been employed by NBC, a unit of General Electric,
since 1977, and has headed NBC's Entertainment Group since 1990.
