FT  02 MAY 91 / International Company News: Sale could raise over CDollars
1bn
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CANADA'S Reichmann family, which controls large property and natural
resources investments, could raise more than CDollars 1bn (USDollars 860m)
from the sale of energy-related companies.
A court ruling earlier this week allows the division of the Calgary-based
Interhome Energy into two parts - Home Oil, an oil and gas producer, and
Interprovincial Pipe Line, Canada's biggest oil pipeline operator. Both
companies are controlled by GW Utilities, in which the Reichmanns have an 89
per cent stake.
GWU said it has been approached by potential buyers for its shares in both
Home and Interprovincial. But Mr Jim Doak, analyst at First Marathon
Securities, said that the sale of Home will be complicated by its debt load.
