FT  02 MAY 91 / Observer: 'Bed' bugged
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Britain's biggest bed-maker Silentnight Holdings is evidently nodding off a
bit after recovering from its disastrous distribution deal with failed
retailer Lowndes Queensway. Silentnight's official Stock Exchange
announcement boasts that while 'many Queensway suppliers incurred sizeable
bed debts, no bad debt was incurred by our group.'
