FT  02 MAY 91 / Parliament and Politics: Unpaid parking fines
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
FOREIGN diplomats and international organisations incurred 6,551 unpaid
parking fines in London last year, the government said.
A Commons written reply showed that the five worst offenders were Poland
with 531 unpaid fines, Saudi Arabia 346, Soviet Union 308, Pakistan 220, and
Kuwait 218.
