FT  02 MAY 91 / Parliament and Politics: Committee scrutiny
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE government has accepted that the work of the Lord Chancellor's
Department and of government law officers should be subject to investigation
by the Commons' Home Affairs select committee.
Mr John MacGregor said yesterday that changes to standing orders would be
proposed to allow the select committee to scrutinise the administration of
courts and tribunals. Individual cases and prosecution policy would be
excluded.
