<HEADLINE>
FT  02 MAY 91 / Survey of Poland (5): Deal yet to be reached with Soviet
Union
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE SITUATION vis-a-vis the Soviet Union is complex in different ways.
At present, Poland owes the Soviet Union 4.7bn transferable roubles and
Dollars 1.7-1.8bn in convertible currency, while the Soviet Union owes
Poland 7.7bn in transferable roubles and Dollars 300m in convertible
currency clearing balances (up to the end of the first quarter of 1991).
Poland argues that its net claims of 3bn transferable roubles should more
than offset its net debt of Dollars 1.4-1.5bn.
If recent precedents with Hungary and Czechoslovakia were followed, Poland
would finish up as a substantial creditor. But agreement has yet to be
reached.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
<PAGE>
London Page III
</PAGE>
