<HEADLINE>
FT  02 MAY 91 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Australian government has come to a decision on the future of the wool
industry, the stockpile, the debt and future administration. The main
recommendations by the Vines committee have been accepted with modest
adjustments. The one of most concern to the industry is that relating to the
stockpile. There is no ban on disposal at the discretion of the committee to
be in control, in the rest of this year; nor is there a trigger point in
prices to permit release or not. The market meanwhile continues to
strengthen in Australia, and a record offering of British wool sold at
auction in Bradford at appreciably higher prices.
</TEXT>
