<HEADLINE>
FT  02 MAY 91 / UK Company News: A&amp;C Black tumbles to Pounds 276,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The deteriorating economic climate, coupled with the postponement of several
important titles, were blamed by A&amp;C Black, the book publisher and
distributor, for a marked decline in profits in the year to end-December.
Turnover increased from Pounds 5.44m to Pounds 6.32m. However, taxable
profits were more than halved to Pounds 276,000 (Pounds 637,000).
Earnings per share came out at 14.5p (31.2p) and directors propose to pay a
final dividend of 8.75p for an unchanged total of 13p.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
<PAGE>
London Page 26
</PAGE>
</DOC>
