<HEADLINE>
FT  02 MAY 91 / UK Company News: Panel censures bidder for Merlin Intl
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JANE FULLER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The bidder for Merlin International Properties and his financial adviser,
Fininvest, have been censured by the Takeover Panel for failing to ensure
that the necessary funds would be available.
The Pounds 2.9m bid, subsequently withdrawn, was made by newly-formed Luirc,
based offshore and owned by Swiss-based Estonia Venture. The money was
supposed to come via a loan from Bonaventure Investments, another offshore
concern.
The panel has criticised Mr Arthur Oaks, Luirc's UK representative, and
Fininvest. It said no announcement should have been made before Fininvest
had received an irrevocable commitment from Bonaventure to provide funds.
General Principle 3 had been offended, which says offers should only be
announced when the bidder is sure it can implement the offer. The principle
also attaches responsibility to the financial adviser.
The panel stressed that particular care was needed 'when a financial adviser
is acting for a newly created offeror, such as an off-the-shelf overseas
company.'
</TEXT>
