<TEXT>
EVEN third best is not bad when it is a diamond weighing 273 carats. Mr Gabi
Tolkowsky (above) was in charge of cutting the De Beers Centenary diamond,
which was unveiled yesterday at the Tower of London. It is third in size
only to the Great Star of Africa and the Lesser Star of Africa, both in the
Crown Jewels. It has taken three years to cut the diamond, insured for
Dollars 100m (Pounds 58m), from a 599-carat rough stone taken from the
Premier Mine in South Africa in 1986.
