FT  01 MAY 91 / UK Company News: Benchmark incurs loss and seeks Pounds 6m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Benchmark, the financial services group, is asking shareholders for Pounds
6m via a rights issue of 107.3m shares at 6p apiece on a 2-for-1 basis. The
group also announced that for the first half of 1990 it incurred a loss of
Pounds 4.95m pre-tax-after exceptional provisions of Pounds 5.05m compared
with previous profits of Pounds 732,000.
As a result group net asset value fell from Pounds 14m as at June 30 1990 to
Pounds 6.5m at the end of December 1990. This would breach loan covenants,
hence the rights issue. Losses per share totalled 9.23p (earnings 0.88p) and
there is no interim dividend - 0.75p was paid previously. The 20p shares are
being sub-divided into one new ordinary of 5p and one deferred of 15p.
