FT  01 MAY 91 / Observer: No holes barred
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Holidaymakers to Eire, beware. The rapid growth in heavy vehicle traffic and
the cuts in public spending have elevated the health of Ireland's road
system to the status of a national joke. Indeed, a popular radio chat show
has started a competition to find the republic's worst pothole.
Brendan McGahon, who represents a border constituency in the Irish
parliament, says: 'Anglers are fishing in them and wild animals we thought
were extinct are actually hiding in them.' A border guard recently warned
motorists approaching potholes to avoid other cars trying to get out of
them.
