FT  01 MAY 91 / Three are charged with fraud
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND HUGHES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THREE FORMER directors of Homes Assured, the mortgage broker which went into
liquidation in 1989 owing Pounds 10m, were yesterday charged with defrauding
the company's creditors, writes Raymond Hughes.
Following an 18-month investigation by the Serious Fraud Office, Mr Anthony
Dobson, Mr Michael Robinson and Mr Keith Woodward were charged at King's
Cross police station in London and bailed to appear at Clerkenwell
magistrates court on May 21.
They were charged that between July 1 1988 and August 31 1989 they were
knowingly parties to the carrying on of the business of Homes Assured with
intent to defraud its creditors, and/or the creditors of another person, or
for another fraudulent purpose, contrary to section 458 of the 1985
Companies Act.
