FT  01 MAY 91 / World Trade News: Untitled Item
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By WILLIAM DULLFORCE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   GENEVA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MOSCOW yesterday was given observer status in Gatt's Anti-Dumping Committee,
marking a further step to eventual membership of the world trade
organisation, William Dullforce reports from Geneva.
Last May it won observer status in Gatt itself, and in March this year
similar standing on Gatt's import licensing committee. Moscow now has access
to two of the codes to which Gatt members subscribe separately, which are
meant mainly to lower non-tariff obstacles to trade.
